summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 20,758, entitled: "An Ordinance providing for the laying off, widening, altering, extending and establishing of Judkins Street, in the City of Seattle, from Thirty-second Avenue South to Thirty-third Avenue South; and providing for the condemnation, appropriation, taking and damaging of land and other property necessary therefor; and providing that the payment for such improvement be made by special assessment upon property specially benefited, in the manner provided by law," approved on the 26th day of April, 1909.
